<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FCDFE4448A75013FE2BFE04" lastPageId="388" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="387" pageNumber="388" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FCDFE4448A75013FBBEFE3F" blockId="387.[151,1436,1855,2025]" lastBlockId="388.[151,1436,151,680]" lastPageId="388" lastPageNumber="389" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCDFE4348A75013FE09F8A8" bold="true" box="[151,428,1855,1880]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FCDFE434ABC5013FCBCF8A7" box="[652,793,1855,1879]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="387" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="2.6">2.6–4.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE434B185013FC35F8A7" box="[808,912,1855,1879]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Holotype</typeStatus>
totally testaceous-ferruginous, except petiole black. Specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18FCDFE43499A5048FE55F88C" box="[426,496,1892,1916]" name="China" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">China</collectingCountry>
, Liuxihe National Forest Park, totally yellow-testaceous, except petiole black. Antenna clavate. Antennal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE434ABB50ABFD48F86F" box="[651,749,1927,1951]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">holotype</typeStatus>
in following proportions: 9:5:15:8:8:6:5.5:5.5:5:8. Head excavated, dull, weakly granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; temple distinct; head of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE434D0A5080FA39F834" box="[1338,1436,1964,1988]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">holotype</typeStatus>
with POL = 2; OL = 1; OOL = 8. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression; in 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCAFE4448A757BBFF5CFF5F" box="[151,249,151,175]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">holotype</typeStatus>
pronotum dull, sculptured by numerous longitudinal striae. Scutum shiny or dull, long and narrow, sculptured by longitudinal keels, without lateral pointed apophyses. Metanotum smooth, shiny, slightly hollow behind scutellum, with sides protruding (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCAFE444A4157F3FD54FF07" box="[625,753,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Plate 120D</figureCitation>
). Lateral protrusions of metanotum rounded. Metathorax + propodeum of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCAFE4449745628FE03FEEC" box="[324,422,260,284]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">holotype</typeStatus>
with anterior surface smooth, shiny, unsculptured, except few very slight longitudinal striae. Posterior surface of propodeum strongly transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron almost completely smooth, unsculptured, occasionally partly transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete. Protarsal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCAFE444A3A5643FDC9FE77" box="[522,620,367,391]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">holotype</typeStatus>
in following proportions: 15:2.5:5.5:17:27. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCAFE444D275643FA36FE77" box="[1303,1427,367,391]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Plate 120E</figureCitation>
) with one large subdistal tooth and one row of 8–11 lamellae + one hair. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCAFE444CEE56B8FAFCFE5C" box="[1246,1369,404,428]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Plate 120E</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 14–22 lamellae; distal apex with 13–24 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FCAFE4448F756F0FE2BFE04" blockId="388.[151,1436,151,680]" box="[199,398,476,500]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCAFE4448F756F0FEAEFE04" bold="true" box="[199,267,476,500]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
